-- BMO Hires Putrino for U.S. Real Estate Banking
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-11-12T21:50:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-12/bmo-hires-putrino-for-u-s-real-estate-banking.html
Bank of Montreal , Canada’s fourth-biggest lender by assets, hired Sachem Street Capital Advisors
LLC’s John Putrino as a managing director for U.S. real estate
investment banking for BMO Capital Markets.  Putrino will be based in  Washington , the firm said today in
an e-mailed statement. Putrino has more than 18 years industry
experience, including as founder and chief executive officer of
Sachem Street and as head of North American lodging and leisure
investment banking at  Credit Suisse Group AG. (CSGN)   BMO has been active in North American real estate for more
than a decade, with Mark Decker leading the group since 2011,
said Martha McInnis, a spokeswoman for the firm.  BMO also hired Joel Fishbein as a senior analyst covering
software companies for the technology, telecommunications and
media-equity research group, according to a separate e-mail.
Fishbein, who was previously with Lazard Capital Markets LLC,
starts Nov. 18 in  New York  and will report to Christine Farkas,
director of U.S. equity research, the firm said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
